#: ../../../policy/CMP0217.rst:2
msgid "CMP0217"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0217.rst:6
msgid "The :prop_dir:`MACROS` directory property does not exist anymore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0217.rst:8
msgid ""
"In CMake 4.3 and below, the macros defined in a directory are registered in "
"the :prop_dir:`MACROS` directory property.  However, the property does not "
"have the same scope as macros, so it does not represent the actual list of "
"macros. In CMake 4.4 and above, this property is not longer filled with the "
"defined macros.  One may still use :command:`if(COMMAND myMacro) "
"<if(COMMAND)>` to test whether one exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0217.rst:15
msgid ""
"The ``OLD`` behavior for this policy is to store macros definition in the :"
"prop_dir:`MACROS` directory property. The ``NEW`` behavior for this policy "
"is to no longer manage the :prop_dir:`MACROS` directory property."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/include/STANDARD_ADVICE.rst:1
msgid ""
"This policy was introduced in CMake version |INTRODUCED_IN_CMAKE_VERSION|. "
"It may be set by :command:`cmake_policy` or :command:"
"`cmake_minimum_required`. If it is not set, CMake |WARNS_OR_DOES_NOT_WARN|, "
"and uses ``OLD`` behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/include/DEPRECATED.rst:2
msgid ""
"The ``OLD`` behavior of a policy is :ref:`deprecated by definition <cmake-"
"policies-intro>` and may be removed in a future version of CMake."
msgstr ""
